ation with farm workers who appear in the book.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEthnology. 0aHealth services accessibility. 0aMexican Americans. 0aMigrant agricultural laborerszUnited StatesxSocial conditions. 0aNoncitizens. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aanthropologist.  aanthropology.  aarizona desert.  abiography.  aborderlands.  acrossing the border.  acultural analysis.  adeportation.  adeported immigrants.  aembodied anthropology.  afarm labor camps.  ahealth and wellness.  ahealth care.  ahuman rights.  aimmigration stories.  aimmigration.  amemoir.  amexican immigrants.  aoaxaca.  asocial inequalities.  aus mexico relations.1 aBourgois, Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095479340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954793423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520954793/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles